usea, vomiting, and visual disturbances.', 'Metabolism', NULL, NULL, 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/100738/', '[1] "Product Information. Kaletra (lopinavir-ritonavir)" Abbott Pharmaceutical, Abbott Park, IL.[2] Bates DE, Herman RJ "Carbamazepine toxicity induced by lopinavir/ritonavir and nelfinavir." Ann Pharmacother 40 (2006): 1190-5[3] Cerner Multum, Inc. "Australian Product Information." O 0[4] Canadian Pharmacists Association "e-CPS. Available from: URL: http://www.pharmacists.ca/function/Subscriptions/ecps.cfm?link=eCPS_quikLink."[5] Department of Health andHuman Services "Guidelines for the Use of Antiretroviral Agents inHIV-1-Infected Adults and Adolescents. Available from: URL: https://aidsinfo.nih.gov/contentfiles/lvguidelines/AdultAndAdolescentGL.pdf." ([2015, April 8]):[6] "Product Information. Tegretol (carbamazepine)." Novartis Pharmaceuticals, East Hanover, NJ.[7] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[8] Barry M, Gibbons S, Back D, Mulcahy F "Protease inhibitors in patients with HIV disease. Clinically important pharmacokinetic considerations." Clin Pharmacokinet 32 (1997): 194-209[9] Bates DE, Herman RJ "Carbamazepine toxicity induced by lopinavir/ritonavir and nelfinavir." Ann Pharmacother 40 (2006): 1190-5[10] Durant J, Clevenbergh P, Garraffo R, Halfon P, Icard S, DelGiudice P, Montagne N, Schapiro JM, Dellamonica P "Importance of protease inhibitor plasma levels in HIV-infected patients treated with genotypic-guided therapy: pharmacological data from the Viradapt Study." Aids 14 (2000): 1333-9[11] Burman W, Orr L "Carbamazepine toxicity after starting combination antiretroviral therapy including ritonavir and efavirenz." Aids 14 (2000): 2793-4[12] Mateu-de Antonio J, Grau S, Gimeno-Bayon JL, Carmona A "Ritonavir-induced carbamazepine toxicity." Ann Pharmacother 35 (2001): 125-6[13] Garcia AB, Ibarra AL, Etessam JP, et al. "Protease inhibitor-induced carbama